compressions: Contains configuration options specific to the compression method used during indexing or querying.
name: The name to associate with this compression configuration.
kind: The compression kind being configured for vector search.
truncationDimension: Number of dimensions to truncate vectors to. Use only for MRL embeddings (e.g., text-embedding-3-large (small)).
enableRescoring: If true, results are rescored using full-precision vectors after initial search on compressed vectors.
defaultOversampling: Oversampling factor (>= 1). Only applicable when rescoring is enabled; higher can improve recall but increases latency.
rescoreStorageMethod: Storage method for original vectors (immutable in the service).
quantizedDataType: For scalar quantization: the target data type for quantized vector values.
